{"questionId":"22641883","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Diego is a teacher in the school. He believes that the number of students, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, who have had influenza during the first&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> days of the school year, can be modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>250</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>240</mn><msup><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Draw a Venn diagram to represent this information.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/b8759ab20e566ed986a9212c106581b6c5fd7a82.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A3</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> in correct place, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> correct, <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> correct. Award at most <em><strong>A0A1A1</strong></em> if the rectangle is omitted. Condone the omission of the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>430</mn></math>, as explicitly asked for in part (b).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22641883","referenceCode":